Tuplex Romania este o companie multinationala, lider european in domeniul distributiei de materiale pentru productie publicitara, constructii si industrie ( www.tuplex.pl/ www.tuplex.ro )

Angajarile se fac in:
- Popesti Leordeni, jud. Ilfov (sediul central Tuplex Romania) - preferam colegi cu domiciliul in sector 3,4,5 sau chiar din Popesti Leordeni
- Cluj Napoca, Parc Logistic ROXER, Calea Baciului nr. 1-3 (filiala Cluj Tuplex Romania)
- Timisoara, Parc Logistic Eurorent, Strada Polona nr. 2 (filiala Timisoara Tuplex Romania)

CERINTE POST:
- cunoasterea limbii romane la un nivel avansat;
- minim studii medii finalizate;
- cunostinte solide de operare PC: WORD, EXCEL, Outlook;
- capacitatea de a acumula rapid cunostinte aprofundate despre produse, piata, concurenta, politici comerciale, proceduri;
- experienta in vanzari B2B;
- experienta in vanzari pe teren;
- experienta in vanzari de materiale de constructii sau materiale destinate productiei/ prelucrarii de orice tip reprezinta avantaj.

CARACTERISTICI PERSONALE:
- persoana comunicativa, sociabila, serioasa si responsabila;
- persoana dedicata activitatii pe care o desfasoara, orientata catre rezultate si clienti.

DESCRIEREA POSTULUI:
- promovarea constanta si consecventa a produselor comercializate de Tuplex;
- activitate de vanzari pe teren;
- gestionarea clientilor activi si dezvoltarea activa a portofoliului de clienti din zona arondata
- acordarea de suport tehnic clientilor
- negocierea preturilor, conditiilor de livrare, modalitatilor si termenelor de plata, respectand politica comerciala Tuplex;
- indeplinirea obiectivelor de vanzari.

AVANTAJE:
- oportunitatea de a lucra si a se dezvolta intr-o echipa tanara de profesionisti;
- reale sanse de colaborare pe termen lung;
- contract de munca legal, din prima zi, cu taxele platite la zi;
- salariu fix, bonuri de masa si bonusuri de performanta.


Va rugam sa trimiteti CV-ul Dumneavoastra la adresa de mail info@tuplex.ro, mentionand pozitia si filiala (Bucuresti, Cluj sau Timisoara) pentru care aplicati, salariul minim solicitat, precum si disponibilitatea de angajare.

We have an open position of Country Manager Assistant, as contractor position, for non-determined period, reporting to Romania Country Manager, located in Bucharest.

Please find below the main responsibilities of the above-mentioned position.

Responsibilities: 

 	Provide full range of administrative support to the Country Manager including, but not limited to, scheduling meetings, managing travel arrangements, processing expense reports, and providing other site-specific assistance;
 	Coordinates the arrangements for meetings, manages and coordinates agenda, books relevant facilities and equipment; attends and takes minutes upon request (e.g. Country Management Forum Meetings, other meetings organized by the Country Manager);
 	Prepare and edit meeting agendas, minutes, action items, and presentations using Microsoft Office;
 	Coordinates registration, travel and accommodation arrangements for the Country Manager and Leadership Team colleagues travelling with the Country Manager;
 	Plans, organizes and prioritizes work on a daily basis in order to meet deadlines;
 	Prepares routine documents as requested by the Country Manager;
 	Manages the Country Manager’s financial/administrative information (e.g. invoices, expense requests, keeping track of budget);
 	Manages financial/administrative information (e.g. invoices, expense requests, keeping track of the team’s budget), checks and validates information; checks for errors/discrepancies.


Skills, Knowledge, Qualifications & Experience:

 	1-3 years previous experience in relevant senior secretarial or administrative role
 	University degree
 	Advanced English level
 	Ability to work under pressure (e.g. cope with multi-tasks) whilst maintaining quality
 	Computer literacy – Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Power Point)
 	Very good ability to plan, organize, prioritize
 	Ability to communicate effectively verbally and in writing
 	Systematic thinking and ability to work according the instructions

We Are Looking for:

Experienced software developer with relevant knowledge of C/C++ for our office in Cluj-Napoca.


The Project:

Our customer provides software solutions to plan, simulate, view in 3D and improve factory production activities, both automated and which require a human worker.

We are working together with the customer’s team in developing and maintaining those products.


Responsibilities:

Development of client requirements, including analyzing the requirements and discussing the technical solution with our client.


Required Competencies:

Mandatory:
• C++ experience
• basic Qt programming experience

Nice to have:
• Experience with CMake and QML
• Computer Graphics know-how
• COM know-how
• AutoCAD know-how (user and/or ObjectArx, ActiveX api)


We Value:

• Respect
• Reliability
• Strive for Excellence 





