- Studii superioare finalizate, preferabil in domeniul economic; 
- O buna cunoastere a limbii engleze (scris si conversatie);
- Abilitati relevante de calcul numeric;
- Atentie la detalii, abilitati organizatorice, responsabilitate si incredere in fortele proprii; promtitudinea si acuratetea sunt deopotriva calitati necesare.
- Abilitati relevante de utilizare Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, etc)

   RESPONSABILITATI

- suport implementare, administrare si monitorizare credite acordate persoanelor juridice ((i) intocmire contracte de credit, de facilitate, de garantie si acte aditionale aferente; (ii) efectuare utilizari/rambursari dupa verificarea documentelor, in conformitate cu aprobarea; (iii) efectuare inregistrari in sistemul informatic al Bancii cu privire la termenii facilitatii de credit; (iv) monitorizare credit, angajamente si garantii)

Responsibilities

• Responsible with finding solutions, temporary remedies and/or reparations in order to maintain and improve the functionality of the systems found under his/her administration;
• Promotes new applications/systems in production, applies various technical tests in the systems;
• Assures support for the use of the applications promoted in production;
• Offers assistance to front line support officers in order to prioritize and solve the incidents/problems regarding to his/her area of expertise and also, when a problem does not frame the first line support officers' abilities, he/she takes over that specific problem and tries to find a solution;
• Escalates the incidents/problems to other support lines or to suppliers, if necessary. Registers the solutions, temporary remedies and the steps taken in order to solve the incident/problem in the registered service. Then he/she notifies the user of the front line support when the incident /problem is concluded, offering procedures if necessary;
• Offers technical information for the projects he/she is involved in;
• Covers all the activities below all by himself/herself;
• Furthermore, he/she has coordination and supervision tasks over the other team members and also over the projects initiated by the team that he/she is part of;
• Makes proposals and optimization plans for the team processes;
• Makes up the plan and coordinates the induction of the new team members.



Requirements:
• University degree;
• Knowledge of the insurance business and technical background (IT);
• At least one year similar experience;
• PC knowledge (Microsoft SQL Server,  Microsoft SQL Database Administration) – medium level;
• Conceptual knowledge of programming languages;
• Project management knowledge (medium level);
• Great English skills.



Soft Skills:
• Attention to detail
• Adaptability
• Flexibility
• Integrity
• Stress – resistance
• Analysis capacity
• Results - orientation

About Connectis
Connectis is a fast growing company that develops software for online identification, authentication and authorization of users at very high security levels. We work in an exciting and fast-growing field, which often hits the news headlines. We want to improve the world by making online identification available for everyone and ensuring that people’s privacy is protected in the best way possible. Connectis is a flat and agile organization. Everyone participates and has a ‘hands on’ mentality. We are an honest and ambitious team of experts that together create a positive working atmosphere. Connectis is located within walking distance of Rotterdam Central Station.

Working at Connectis means
 • Team spirit
 • Flexible approach to (free) time and leave
 • Personal contribution to mission critical software used by millions of people
 • Ample opportunity to learn new skills.

The job
